  "Molecule design is decoupled from mechanism: CI-PAM-1f is selected on physicochemical/CNS-MPO/QED criteria with no binding model, docking, or structural rationale tying it to the NDUFA6/Q-module interface; the 'G60D-mimetic hydroxyl arm' is asserted, not demonstrated.",
  "Central biological risk acknowledged but unresolved: G60D proves an activating conformation exists, not that a small-molecule-inducible pocket exists -- the whole PAM premise could be undruggable.",
